Context:
- The original ExtractRewardProgram screen uses BasicScreen (SafeAreaView), ApiError, FiltersBottomSheet, PointsInfoBottomSheet — all depend on native modules that can't render in Storybook web
- So the story manually recreates the UI using DS components directly (same approach as PointsScreen.stories.tsx)
- processPointsExtractData from extract.repository.ts is used to group transactions by date and map to ListCardTransition format
- Store is seeded using pointsExtractActions from the mocked Zustand store

Screenshots confirm:
- Loaded: Shows 15,320 points, date-grouped transactions (20 de fevereiro, 18 de fevereiro, 15 de fevereiro, 12 de fevereiro)
- Empty: Shows 500 points, tabs but no transactions
- Loading: Shows skeleton loading in CardPoints and search area
- Error: Shows "Algo deu errado!" with error icon

Give a concise review with actionable items.

